            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Set service areas accurately in Google Business Profile and build location-specific landing pages for each zone. Google uses the declared service area alongside physical location to determine coverage.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is centroid bias?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Centroid bias is Google's historical tendency to favour businesses near the geographic centre of a city or neighbourhood. Post-Vicinity Update, exact proximity to the searcher matters more than proximity to the centroid.</p></div></div>
